N grstyle.pkg
D  4 Feb 2022
U 1
d 'GRSTYLE': module to customize the overall look of graphs
d 
d  grstyle allows you to customize the overall look of graphs from
d within a do-file without having to fiddle around with external
d scheme files. The advantage of grstyle over manually editing a
d scheme file is that everything needed to reproduce your graphs
d can be included in a single do-file.
d 
d KW: graphics
d KW: scheme files
d KW: custom graphics
d KW: plot
d 
d Requires: Stata version 9.2 and palettes from SSC (q.v.)
d 
d Distribution-Date: 20200919
d 
d Author: Ben Jann, University of Bern
d Support: email jann@@soz.unibe.ch
d 
f g\grstyle.ado
f g\grstyle.hlp
f g\grstyle_set.ado
f g\grstyle_set.hlp
e
S http://www.rogernewsonresources.org.uk/stata16
N xsvmat.pkg
D  4 Feb 2022
U 2
d xsvmat: Convert a matrix to variables in an output dataset
d xsvmat is an extended version of svmat.  It creates an output
d dataset (or resultsset), with one observation per row of either an
d existing matrix or the result of a matrix expression, and data on
d the values of the column entries in that row, and, optionally,
d extra variables specified by the user.  The output dataset created
d by xsvmat may be listed to the Stata log, or saved to a data
d frame, or saved to a disk file, or written to the memory
d (overwriting any pre-existing dataset).
d 
d Author: Roger Newson
d Distribution-Date: 11april2020
d Stata-Version: 16
f x\xsvmat.ado
f x\xsvmat.sthlp
e
